            <subdebate.1>
                <subdebateinfo>
                    <title>REGULATION OF INTERSTATE FREIGHTS</title>
                    <page.no>8436</page.no>
                </subdebateinfo>
                <question>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8436</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K2D</name.id>
                            <electorate>TASMANIA</electorate>
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">READY, Rudolph</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator READY</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Will the Assistant Minister, <inline font-weight="bold">Senator Russell,</inline> say what action the Government propose to take under the War Precautions Act for the regulation  of freights on Inter-State steam-ships throughout Australia? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </question>
                <answer>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8436</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K3E</name.id>
                            <electorate>VICTORIA</electorate>
                            <party>ALP</party>
                            <role>Assistant Minister</role>
                            <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">RUSSELL, Edward</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator RUSSELL</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Some action has already been taken in this regard. I think it was on the 8th July last that it was made illegal to increase freights on coastal services beyond what they were at that date. The matter is under the consideration of the Prices Adjustment Board and the Customs and Navy Departments. At a later stage I hope to be able to give the honorable senator the conclusions of the conference of these bodies. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </answer>
            </subdebate.1>
            <subdebate.1>
                <subdebateinfo>
                    <title>POST-OFFICE MOTOR CARS: BRISBANE</title>
                    <page.no>8437</page.no>
                </subdebateinfo>
                <question>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8437</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K7D</name.id>
                            <electorate>QUEENSLAND</electorate>
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">STEWART, James</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator STEWART</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Is the Minister representing the Postmaster-General in a position to reply to the question I put to him on the subject of motor cars used by the Post and Telegraph Department at Brisbane ? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </question>
                <answer>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8437</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>KKZ</name.id>
                            <electorate>NEW SOUTH WALES</electorate>
                            <party>ALP</party>
                            <role>Vice-President of the Executive Council</role>
                            <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">GARDINER, Albert</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator GARDINER</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- I have now the information for which the honorable senator asked. The honorable senator&#39;s questions were - </para>
                    </talk.start>
                    <list type="decimal-dotted">
                        <item label="1.">
                            <para>The original cost of the motor cars used in clearing the postal pillar-boxes in and around the city of Brisbane. </para>
                        </item>
                        <item label="2.">
                            <para>The cost of repairs for the past two years. </para>
                        </item>
                        <item label="3.">
                            <para>The cost of relief cars, during repairs, for the past two years. </para>
                        </item>
                        <item label="4.">
                            <para>The total cost of the service during the past two years. </para>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                    <para class="block">The following information, in reply to these questions, has been furnished by the Deputy Postmaster-General, Brisbane :  - </para>
                    <list type="decimal-dotted">
                        <item label="1.">
                            <para>Original cost of two (2) motor cars, &#163;650. </para>
                        </item>
                        <item label="2.">
                            <para>Repairs, new parts, &#163;574. </para>
                        </item>
                        <item label="3.">
                            <para>Hire of relief cars, &#163;390. </para>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                    <para class="block">
                        <graphic href="079332191609064_1_0.jpg" />
                    </para>
                    <para>The above information is for two years ended 30th June, 1916, since when a third car, costing &#163;240, was put into commission. </para>
                    <para>No. 2 car is now undergoing repairs, at a cost of &#163;156. </para>
                </answer>
            </subdebate.1>
