            <subdebate.1>
                <subdebateinfo>
                    <title>WHEAT POOL</title>
                    <page.no>8437</page.no>
                </subdebateinfo>
                <question>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8437</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>KRZ</name.id>
                            <electorate>WESTERN AUSTRALIA</electorate>
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">LYNCH, Patrick</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator LYNCH</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Is <inline font-weight="bold">Senator Russell,</inline> as the Minister dealing with the wheat pool, in a position to make the statement which he promised to make concerning the payment of the extra 6d. per bushel to farmers concerned in the wheat pool? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </question>
                <answer>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8437</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K3E</name.id>
                            <electorate>VICTORIA</electorate>
                            <party>ALP</party>
                            <role>Assistant Minister</role>
                            <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">RUSSELL, Edward</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator RUSSELL</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- I am glad to be in a position to make <inline font-weight="bold">Senator Lynch</inline> happy at last. The extra 6d. per bushel has been secured, and it is only now a matter of fixing up details of the agreement between the Wheat Board and the States. The money will be paid almost immediately. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                    <interjection>
                        <talk.start>
                            <talker>
                                <page.no>8437</page.no>
                                <time.stamp />
                                <name.id>KRZ</name.id>
                                <electorate />
                                <party />
                                <role />
                                <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                                <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                                <name role="metadata">LYNCH, Patrick</name>
                                <name role="display">Senator Lynch</name>
                            </talker>
                            <para>- What about Western Australia ? </para>
                        </talk.start>
                    </interjection>
                    <continue>
                        <talk.start>
                            <talker>
                                <page.no>8437</page.no>
                                <time.stamp />
                                <name.id>K3E</name.id>
                                <electorate />
                                <party />
                                <role />
                                <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                                <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                                <name role="metadata">RUSSELL, Edward</name>
                                <name role="display">Senator RUSSELL</name>
                            </talker>
                            <para>- I did not wish to refer to Western Australia. By some means Western Australia got 3d. per bushel more than she was entitled to, and we are going to adjust that. </para>
                        </talk.start>
                    </continue>
                    <interjection>
                        <talk.start>
                            <talker>
                                <page.no>8438</page.no>
                                <time.stamp />
                                <name.id>KRZ</name.id>
                                <electorate />
                                <party />
                                <role />
                                <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                                <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                                <name role="metadata">LYNCH, Patrick</name>
                                <name role="display">Senator Lynch</name>
                            </talker>
                            <para>- The &#34;Western Australian Government did not cash the certificates. </para>
                        </talk.start>
                    </interjection>
                </answer>
            </subdebate.1>
