                        <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                        <name role="metadata">PEARCE, George</name>
                        <name role="display">Senator PEARCE</name>
                    </talker>
                    <para>.- I move - </para>
                </talk.start>
                <quote>
                    <para>That the Senate, at its rising, adjourn until 3 p.m. on Wednesday next. </para>
                </quote>
                <para class="block">Circumstances have delayed the return of the Prime Minister from Sydney, and he is, therefore, unable to meet Parliament to-day. He proposes to return to Melbourne to-morrow, and to leave the same afternoon for Adelaide. The Prime Minister is anxious to be present in another place when the debate on the Ministerial statement of policy in connexion with the war takes place, and the Government, therefore, asks the Senate to adjourn from to-day until Wednesday next, at 3 o&#39;clock. </para>
                <para class="block">Question resolved in the affirmative. </para>
            </speech>
